```json
{
  "application": "CycleGAN",
  "software": [
    "Python",
    "Anaconda3",
    "CycleGAN"
  ],
  "resources": {
    "cluster": "SLURM",
    "partition": "p2",
    "qos": "gpuultimate",
    "gpu": "1",
    "nodes": "1",
    "tasks": "1",
    "cpus_per_task": "4",
    "memory": "64GB",
    "datasets": "datasets/cycleGAN"
  }
}
```

This script utilizes the CycleGAN framework, a deep learning model for image-to-image translation. It is implemented in Python, leveraging the Anaconda3 environment and specifically the CycleGAN package.  The script uses the SLURM cluster management system to run on a high-performance computing environment. It specifies resource requirements for a single GPU, one node, and four CPUs per task, utilizing the "p2" partition with the "gpuultimate" quality of service setting. The script requires 64GB of memory and access to the "datasets/cycleGAN" directory.
